// Reserved keywords cannot be used as method names because the
// `var` token excludes globally-reserved words (`new` is one). The
// snapshot will show a Fail outcome with ERROR nodes -- this
// documents the rejection. If we ever want to relax this (and let
// `x!new(...)` work), we'd need a separate non-reserved token for
// the method-name slot.
new x in {
  x!new(1).
}
